{{Infobox artwork | title = Tony Gwynn | other_language_1 = | other_title_1 = | other_language_2 = | other_title_2 = | wikidata = | image = File:R.I.P., Mr. Padre. -TonyGwynn (14759406044).jpg | image_upright = | alt = | caption = The statue in 2014 | artist = William Behrends | year = {{start date|2007}} | completion_date = <!-- For a more specific date (post-1583): {{start date|YYYY|MM|DD|df=y}} --> | catalogue = | medium = [[Bronze sculpture]] | movement = | subject = [[Tony Gwynn]] | height_metric = <!-- (i.e. in metric units) --> | width_metric = | length_metric = | diameter_metric = | height_imperial = <!-- (i.e. in imperial units) --> | width_imperial = | length_imperial = | diameter_imperial = | dimensions = | dimensions_ref = | metric_unit = cm <!-- Note: this parameter must either use the value given or not be included --> | imperial_unit = in <!-- Note: this parameter must either use the value given or not be included --> | weight = | designation = | condition = | museum = | city = [[San Diego]], California, U.S. | coordinates = {{coord|32.70876|-117.15665|format=dms|type:landmark_region:US-CA|display=inline,title}} | owner = | accession = | preceded_by = <!-- preceding work by the same artist --> | followed_by = <!-- next work by the same artist --> | module = | website = <!-- Official webpage/site only: {{URL|example.com}} --> }} '''''Tony Gwynn''''' is a [[bronze sculpture]] by [[William Behrends]] depicting the [[Tony Gwynn|professional baseball player of the same name]], installed outside [[San Diego]]'s [[Petco Park]], in the [[U.S. state]] of [[California]].
==Description== The bronze statue is 9.5 feet tall. An inscription on the front of the statue's base reads, "Tony Gwynn, Mr. Padre". The reverse side of the base has an inscription by Gwynn's father: "If you work hard, good things will happen."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.petcoparkinsider.com/gwynn-statue-coming-to-petco-park |title=Tony Gwynn statue coming |publisher=Petco Park Insider |date=2007-07-21 |accessdate=2017-05-13}}</ref>
==History== The sculpture was installed in 2007.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espn.com/mlb/news/story?id=2944926 |title=Gwynn 'thrilled to death' with statue at Petco Park |publisher=ESPN |date=2007-07-21 |accessdate=2017-05-13}}</ref>
Fans gathered at the sculpture to pay tribute to Gwynn, following his death in 2014.<ref>{{cite web|last=Laws |first=Will |url=http://m.mlb.com/news/article/80134400/fans-pay-tribute-to-tony-gwynn-at-petco-park-statue/ |title=Fans pay tribute to Tony Gwynn at Petco Park statue |publisher=Major League Baseball |date=2016-01-20 |accessdate=2017-05-13}}</ref>
